<P>"What &s;acrilegious foot&s;teps," cried
<PB N="159" REF="160">
the prie&s;t "thus rudely violate this holy
placed?"</P>
<P>Ellena was now in&s;en&s;ible; and the men|continuing
to advance, Vivaldi drew his
&s;word to protect her.</P>
<P>The prie&s;t and Vivaldi now &s;poke toge|ther,
