<HEAD>CHAP. VIII.</HEAD>
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q><L>And yet I fear you;for you are fatal then,</L>
<L>When your eyes roll &s;o.</L>
<L>Alas! why gnaw you &s;o your nether lip?</L>
<L>Some bloody pa&s;&s;ion &s;hakes your very frame:</L>
<L>The&s;e are portents; but yet I hope, I hope,</L>
<L>They do not point on me.</L></Q>
<BIBL>SHAKSPEARE.</BIBL>
